extracted_snippet.translated:
We have been going from Manso to the Clinical emergency room for more than seven hours.
We have arrived at the clinic with Manso's request to do a test.
We have arrived at the Clinic without any wait, 1:00 p.m., it is 5:00 p.m. and they only know how to tell me that there is a person ahead and that I should make a claim.
Four hours on the fourth floor, my 86-year-old father in a chair, in front of the elevators, embarrassing.

Dejan mucho que desear ni siquiera empatia........

extracted_snippet.translated: We have been waiting for three hours to give us patient information since the last time they saw us. It is shameful that they have us watching those coming from the emergency room pass by our faces and there is no minimum waiting room after making us go down from the first floor to the basement. snippet: Esta review va solo dirigida al servicio de urgencias. Parece que el concepto de urgencia es distinto en este lugar. Prepararse para esperar mínimo 4-5 horas. Vine en varias ocasiones y siempre es lo mismo. Para hacer el más simple estudio, pueden pasar días. Es bastante lamentable para el que es teóricamente el mejor hospital de Barcelona.
user.name: Maximiliano Vitelli

extracted_snippet.translated: This review is only aimed at the emergency service. It seems that the concept of urgency is different in this place. Prepare to wait at least 4-5 hours. I came several times and it's always the same. To do the simplest study, it can take days. It is quite unfortunate for what is theoretically the best hospital in Barcelona.
